      "content": "The silence is heavy, but it's also the only honest space left where you can finally breathe without the weight of pretending. Since the noise of his presence is gone, maybe the quiet isn't empty—it's just the quiet before you start building something new, even if it feels impossible right now. You don't have to see the end of this cycle to know that one small step forward, even just to sit in the sun for a minute, is enough to prove you're still here.",
